<% const path = "../../../"; %>
<%- include("../../_include/_header", {
    "title": "tool-usage.controller.title",
    "description": "tool-usage.controller.description",
    "path": path,
}); %>

<%- include("../_base-header", {
    "path": path
}); %>

<div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9">
    <div>
      <h3>Controller Area</h3>
      <p>${{ tool-usage.controller.description }}$</p>

      <h4>Stage Setting</h4>
      <p>Set the width, height, frame rate, and background color of the display area (Stage).</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/stage-setting.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>Object Setting</h4>
      <p>Set the name and symbol of the display object. The name can be accessed with this.[[name]] in javaScript, and the symbol can be used as a class.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/object-setting.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>Transform</h4>
      <p>Controls the width, height, scaling, and rotation of the displayed object.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/transform.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>Color Transform</h4>
      <p>Add and subtract red, green, blue, and transparency.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/color-transform.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>Blend Mode</h4>
      <p>Blending mode can be used to create compound images. "Compounding" is the process of changing the transparency or color interaction of multiple overlapping objects. Blending allows you to blend colors in overlapping movie clips to create unique effects.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/blend-mode.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>Filters</h4>
      <p>Filters can be used to add high quality visual effects to text, and movie clips. You can also use motion tweening to animate the filter you apply.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/filters.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>Library</h4>
      <p>The library can load images (jpeg, gif, png), sounds (mp3), videos (mp4), and SWF files as external data. Vector drawings, text, and movie clips created on the screen can also be managed.</p>

      <h4>Sound</h4>
      <p>Play the loaded sound data at any frame.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/sound.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>

      <h4>JavaScript</h4>
      <p>It is possible to check the list of JavaScript embedded in the frame.</p>
      <p><a href="<%= path %>${{ main.lang }}$/usage/controller/javascript.html">${{ main.read-more }}$</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

<%- include("../_base-footer", {
    "path": path
}); %>